Problem Statement

Develop a Java application using multilevel inheritance to represent hospital staff. Create a Person class, derive a Doctor class from it, and further derive a Surgeon class. Display the details of the surgeon including name, 
specialization, hospital name, and years of experience.

class Person {

    String name = "Raghul";

}

class Doctor extends Person {

    String hospital = "KSR Hospital";

}

class Surgeon extends Doctor {

    String specialization = "General Surgeon";
    int experience = 8;

    void display() {

        System.out.println("Hospital Details");
        System.out.println("------------------------");
        System.out.println("Name           : " + name);
        System.out.println("Hospital       : " + hospital);
        System.out.println("Specialization : " + specialization);
        System.out.println("Experience     : " + experience + " Years");

    }
}

public class HospitalManagement {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Surgeon s = new Surgeon();

        s.display();

    }
}

Output
